b'[<p><i><b>Ultimate Fight Night 5</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on June 28, 2006.  The event took place at <a href="/wiki/Hard_Rock_Hotel_and_Casino_(Las_Vegas)" title="Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)">Hard Rock Hotel and Casino</a>, in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Las_Vegas,_Nevada" title="Las Vegas, Nevada">Las Vegas, Nevada</a> and was broadcast live on <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Spike_TV" title="Spike TV">Spike TV</a> in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> and <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a>.  \n</p>, <p>The show drew a 1.4 overall rating<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup> and served as the lead-in for the premiere of <i><a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Blade:_The_Series" title="Blade: The Series">Blade: The Series</a></i>. This event featured the UFC debut of future middleweight champion <a href="/wiki/Anderson_Silva" title="Anderson Silva">Anderson Silva</a> and also featured the first of 2 fights between future welterweight stars <a href="/wiki/Jon_Fitch" title="Jon Fitch">Jon Fitch</a> and <a href="/wiki/Thiago_Alves_(fighter)" title="Thiago Alves (fighter)">Thiago Alves</a> . The disclosed fighter payroll for the event was $197,000.\n</p>, <p><br/>\n</p>]'